This article refers to professor William Baylis' researches and shows a surprising similarity between properties of paravectors and vectors in the Euclidean space. It can be confusing at first to get used to a column notation of paravectors, but this form has proved to be the most adequate. The main advantage of this notation is a transparency of mathematical transformations. The author hopes that in future paravector formalism will replace the multivectors formalism in physics as simpler, more intuitive and imaginable. The results presented in this article justify it fully.
